  "texts": [
    "During protocol optimization, we noticed that crosslinking the cDNA molecules immediately after reversetranscription to a polyacrylamide (PA) gel enhances the RiboSoma signal (Supplementary Fig. 1a) suggesting better retention of cDNA in situ throughout the DART-FISH protocol.",
    "This cDNA embedding strategy also led to 1.5-fold median increase of the feature count per gene (Supplementary Fig. 1b, c), compared to when the polyacrylamide gel is cast after RCA.",
    "Thus, RiboSoma serves as a marker for cDNA content of the tissue and provides a quality control for in situ reactions.",
    "Following gel embedding and RNA digestion, cDNA molecules are hybridized with a library of padlock probes and circularized at a high temperature to ensure specificity 29, 30.",
    "On their backbone, padlock probes carry a universal sequence used for amplification and genespecific barcodes."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
